      <div class="bylaws-content">
        <div class="bylaws-intro">
          <p>Oakville regulates short-term accommodations (STAs) under By-law 2018-045. The town has a comprehensive demerit point system to ensure compliance. Here's what you need to operate legally.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bylaws-grid">
          <div class="bylaw-card highlight-card">
            <h3>Demerit Point System</h3>
            <p>Oakville uses a demerit point system for violations. Accumulating <strong>7+ points results in license suspension</strong>, and <strong>15+ points means license revocation</strong>. Points are assigned for various violations including noise complaints, parking issues, and bylaw non-compliance. We monitor your listing to help you avoid demerits.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bylaw-card">
            <h3>28-Day Maximum Stay</h3>
            <p>Short-term accommodation in Oakville is defined as rentals of 28 consecutive days or less. Rentals of 29+ days are considered long-term and exempt from STA regulations.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bylaw-card">
            <h3>License Required - $237/Year</h3>
            <p>All STA operators must obtain a license from the Town. The annual fee is approximately $237. Licenses expire on October 31 each year and must be renewed.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bylaw-card">
            <h3>Principal Residence Only</h3>
            <p>Short-term rentals must be your principal residence. Investment properties cannot be used for STAs. You can rent a maximum of 3 lodging units within your home.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bylaw-card">
            <h3>$2 Million Insurance</h3>
            <p>Operators must maintain liability insurance of at least $2,000,000 that specifically covers short-term rental activity.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bylaw-card">
            <h3>Local Contact Required</h3>
            <p>You must have a local contact person available within 1 hour of your property at all times during guest stays. This can be you, a property manager, or a designated representative.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bylaw-card">
            <h3>Renter's Code of Conduct</h3>
            <p>Oakville requires a signed Renter's Code of Conduct from every guest. This document outlines noise rules, parking requirements, and occupancy limits. We handle this automatically.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bylaw-card">
            <h3>4% Municipal Accommodation Tax</h3>
            <p>Oakville charges a 4% MAT on all short-term rentals. This is typically collected and remitted automatically by platforms like Airbnb.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bylaws-cta">
